    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-01-28T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-28T08:00:00-05:00" n="110"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/1–2851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gifford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-01-28T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >January 28, 1951—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4162. Although he has not cleared with Cabinet Attlee has now agreed to voting in
                    favor of paragraph 8 of US resolution with the additional language quoted in
                    paragraph 3 <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 3557, January 27 on
                    understanding (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) that US will not put obstacles in way
                    of those nations which feel that negotiations are still possible or useful and
                        (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) that if Asian-Arab resolution is introduced with
                    Pierson [<hi rend="italic">Pearson</hi>] amendment<note n="1" xml:id="d110fn1"
                        >The reference here is to the plan outlined to the First Committee on
                        January 26 by Lester Pearson of Canada; see footnote 3, <ref
                            target="#pg_128">p. 128</ref>.</note> embodied in it US will not
                        oppose.<note n="2" xml:id="d110fn2">Telegram 4167, January 29, from London,
                        reported Cabinet endorsement for Attlee’s approval of Paragraph 8 of the
                        U.S. draft resolution with the additional language (795.00/1–2951).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Department pass <gloss target="#t_USUN2">USUN</gloss>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                    </hi> as London 67.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gifford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
